os.system("code")  # opens VS Code if 'code' command is recognized


If VS Code is not added to PATH, this will not work and youâ€™ll need to use the full path with os.startfile().

âœ… Key difference:
Method	Path required?	Example
os.startfile()	Yes	Chrome, PyCharm, any app
os.system()	Sometimes	VS Code (code), terminal commands

So bro, in your code:

Chrome â†’ uses os.startfile() with path âœ…

VS Code â†’ uses os.system("code"), which works only if VS Code was added to PATH during installation

